uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.filter

Class OrFilter<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.filter.FilterSet<T>
      • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.filter.OrFilter<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AcceptFilter<T>, BaseFilter<T>, BinaryFilter<T>, Targetted<T>

    public final class OrFilter<T>
extends FilterSet<T>
implements AcceptFilter<T>, BinaryFilter<T>
    A generic combining filter that can combine both BaseSQLFilters and AcceptFilters in an OR combination. To do this it has to convert everything into AcceptFilters using separate SQL queries for each component BaseSQLFilter. Though pure SQLFilters can be combined as a SQLOrFilter and checked as a single query. This can make this kind of filter very expensive and prevents the use of joins etc. These filters should be avoided in performance critical queries like report generation however they are still useful as a way of simplifying complex combinational logic that would be just as inefficient if written by hand. The actual accept/reject operation is implemented by a nested FilterMatcher (usually the factory class).
